10    /**
11    * An appender that generates the byte code for a given method. This is done by writing the byte code instructions to
12    * the given ASM {@link org.objectweb.asm.MethodVisitor}.
13    * <p>&nbsp;</p>
14    * The {@code ByteCodeAppender} is not allowed to write
15    * annotations to the method or call the {@link org.objectweb.asm.MethodVisitor#visitCode()},
16    * {@link org.objectweb.asm.MethodVisitor#visitMaxs(int, int)} or {@link org.objectweb.asm.MethodVisitor#visitEnd()}
17    * methods which is both done by the entity delegating the call to the {@code ByteCodeAppender}. This is done in order
18    * to allow for the concatenation of several byte code appenders and therefore a more modular description of method
19    * implementations.
20    */
